#!/usr/bin/env testml


*jsc.validate(*json) == *valid


=== Test 1 - validation of host names - a valid host name
--- valid: true
--- jsc
{"format": "hostname"}
--- json
"www.example.com"


=== Test 2 - validation of host names - a valid punycoded IDN hostname
--- valid: true
--- ^jsc
--- json
"xn--4gbwdl.xn--wgbh1c"


=== Test 3 - validation of host names - a host name starting with an illegal character
--- valid: false
--- ^jsc
--- json
"-a-host-name-that-starts-with--"


=== Test 4 - validation of host names - a host name containing illegal characters
--- valid: false
--- ^jsc
--- json
"not_a_valid_host_name"


=== Test 5 - validation of host names - a host name with a component too long
--- valid: false
--- ^jsc
--- json
"a-vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvveeeeeeeeeeeeeeeerrrrrrrrrrrrrrrryyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy-long-host-name-component"


# vim: ft=testml sw=2:
